.TH DICTEE-AUDIO-SOURCES "1" "April 2026" "dictee 1.3.0"
.SH NAME
dictee-audio-sources \- list available PipeWire audio sources for dictee
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dictee-audio-sources
.SH DESCRIPTION
Lists all available audio input sources from PipeWire in a machine-readable format.
Used by the KDE plasmoid and dictee-setup to populate audio source selection menus.
.SH OUTPUT FORMAT
One line per source, pipe-separated:
.PP
.B value|icon|label
.TP
.I value
Source identifier: empty for system default, node name for hardware sources,
\fBapp:\fIname\fR for application streams.
.TP
.I icon
Freedesktop icon name (e.g., audio-input-microphone, firefox).
.TP
.I label
Human-readable description.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.nf
|audio-input-microphone|System default
alsa_input.usb-...|audio-input-microphone|USB Microphone
alsa_output.pci-...monitor|audio-speakers|Monitor: Built-in Audio
app:firefox|firefox|Firefox \(em YouTube
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dictee-setup (1),
.BR pw-dump (1)
